  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Re-read notes/04 to inventory ADOPT and PARTIAL surfaces; note DON'T ADOPT surfaces</step>
    <step>Re-read ADR-013 §"Exceptions" — the 4-criteria gate for non-BFF deployables; ADR-001 §Functions scope</step>
    <step>For each ADOPT/PARTIAL surface: evaluate the 4 ADR-013 criteria explicitly (latency coupling? transactional coupling? bounded surface? component-duplication?). Recommend deployment model. Cite criteria results</step>
    <step>For deployment models other than in-process BFF: state additional considerations — MCP server scaling, Function event-driven trigger pattern, Foundry Agent hosting + cost</step>
    <step>Aggregate migration cost: across all ADOPT/PARTIAL surfaces, sum estimated dev effort. Identify shared infrastructure changes (e.g., "all 4 adopt-surfaces require lifting middleware from per-instance to IChatClient.AsBuilder().Use*() composition — this is one shared infra change, not four separate ones")</step>
    <step>Publish-size analysis: enumerate new NuGet refs implied by adoption — Microsoft.Agents.AI.*, Microsoft.Agents.AI.Foundry, Microsoft.Agents.AI.Workflows if applicable. Estimate compressed size delta. Flag if exceeds bff-extensions.md baseline tolerance</step>
    <step>Risk register: 5-10 risks across adopt-surfaces. For each: surface(s) affected, mitigation, severity</step>
    <step>Reversibility analysis per adopt-surface: if adoption goes badly, what's the rollback path? (this informs §8 open questions in the synthesis)</step>
    <step>Write notes/05-deployment-and-migration.md with sections: Deployment-model recommendations (per surface) | Shared infrastructure changes | Publish-size impact | Risk register | Reversibility analysis | DON'T ADOPT surfaces (one line each — "no migration")</step>
    <step>Commit: `docs(assessment): deployment + migration analysis (R1 task 005)`</step>
  </steps>
